title.@value: Fetus or newborn affected by other malpresentation, malposition or disproportion during labour or delivery

definition.@value: A condition characterised by findings in the fetus or newborn due to abnormal positions of the vertex of the fetal head (malposition) or any presentation position of the fetus other than vertex of the fetal head, first (malpresentation) during labour and delivery.
